revision.text:
'''Kitazuka Kofun''' (北塚古墳) is a kofun (ancient Kofun) located in {{ill|Ekiya, Fukuyama|ja|駅家町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ekiya, Fukuyama|qq=}}, [[:en:Fukuyama, Hiroshima|Fukuyama]], [[:en:Hiroshima Prefecture|Hiroshima Prefecture]], Japan. It is designated as a Hiroshima Prefecture Historic Site.

== Overview == 
[[File:Kitazuka Kofun, sekkan 3D-B.jpg|thumb|300px|right|{{center|House-shaped stone coffin (top view)}}]]
[[File:Kitazuka Kofun, sekkan 3D-N.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|House-shaped stone coffin (expanded view)}}]]
The Kitazuka Kofun is situated in the eastern part of Hiroshima Prefecture, on the edge of a hill facing a valley north of the Hattori Reservoir in the {{ill|Fukuyama Plain|lt=Kambe Plain|ja|神辺平野|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuyama Plain|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 福山平野}}. The mound itself has been leveled, and a trial excavation was conducted in 1982.<ref name="福山市">[https://www.city.fukuyama.hiroshima.jp/soshiki/bunka/64159.html 北塚古墳] (Fukuyama City official website).</ref>

The original shape of the mound remains uncertain. The burial facility consists of a house-shaped stone coffin made of [[:en:Granite|granite]], or possibly the coffin section of a {{ill|yokoguchi-style stone chamber|ja|横口式石槨|1=Side-entrance Sarcophagus Chamber|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/yokoguchi-style stone chamber|13=User:Immanuelle/Side-entrance Sarcophagus Chamber|qq=}}.<ref name="広島県"/> The coffin is composed of six precisely cut stones, measuring 2.34 meters in length, 1.41 meters in width, and 0.56 meters in height.<ref name="広島県"/> Its lid stone features a rounded rectangular shape, with decorations resembling degraded projections for securing ropes.<ref name="説明板"/> Excavated items include iron nails and fragments of [[:en:Sue pottery|Sue pottery]], such as cups.<ref name="説明板"/> 

The kofun is believed to have been built during the late 7th century,<ref name="説明板">Historic Site Information Board.</ref> or possibly the early 7th century.<ref>{{Harvid|日本古墳大辞典|1=Comprehensive Dictionary of Japanese Kofun|1989}}</ref> It represents an earlier phase of {{ill|yokoguchi-style stone chamber|ja|横口式石槨|1=Side-entrance Sarcophagus Chamber|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/yokoguchi-style stone chamber|13=User:Immanuelle/Side-entrance Sarcophagus Chamber|qq=}} development, exemplified by the {{ill|Inoko Kofun|ja|猪ノ子古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inoko Kofun|qq=}} in Fukuyama.<ref name="広島県"/> 

In 1988, the site was designated a Hiroshima Prefecture Historic Site.<ref name="広島県">[https://www.pref.hiroshima.lg.jp/site/bunkazai/bunkazai-data-206121090.html 北塚古墳] (Hiroshima Prefecture Board of Education).</ref> 
<gallery>
Kitazuka Kofun, sekkan-2.jpg|Stone coffin, side view
Kitazuka Kofun, sekkan-1.jpg|Coffin lid stone<br/>{{small|Left side shows rope-like projection decorations.}}
Kitazuka Kofun, sekkan-5.jpg|Interior of stone coffin<br/>{{small|Carved details visible on lid stone and inner surfaces.}}
</gallery>

== Cultural Properties == 
=== Hiroshima Prefecture Designated Cultural Properties === 
* Historic Site:
''' Kitazuka Kofun - designated on December 26, 1988.<ref name="広島県"/>

